<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-02-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-02-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="537" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d537">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                van Limburg</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-02-09"><hi rend="italic">February</hi> 9, 1865.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 20th ultimo, relative to the capture of the
                            Netherlands ship Geziena Hildegonda, and to inform you that I have
                            submitted a translation thereof for consideration to the Secretary of
                            the Navy.</p>
                        <p>Accept, sir, a renewed assurance of my high consideration.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Roest van Limburg</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,&amp;c.,&amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>